**This is the bug!** 

The `<li>` element for each saving throw has the class:
```
"inline cursor-pointer font-bold text-blood after:content-[',_'] last:after:content-[] hover:text-black dark:hover:text-fog"
```

The **comma is added via CSS `after:content-[',_']`** on the same `<li>` element that has `text-blood` (red color) and `font-bold`. This means the **comma inherits the red bold styling** from the `<li>` element!

When you hover over a saving throw modifier, the `hover:text-black` class changes the text color to black, but the **comma's `::after` pseudo-element also inherits this hover color change**! So the comma turns black on hover, but it also starts out red and bold (when not hovering).

